<para xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
      version="5.0"
      xml:id="resources.information.concepts.design.patterns.classical.structural.adapter.introParagraph">

  Generally one aims to decouple from particular implementations by specifying a generic
  interface. At times, different development teams may define different interfaces for
  the same domain. In such case, we likely have to convert message flows from one interface to
  another. It is in these situations where an adapter may become handy.
</para>